        "header": "3A Program-Centered Task Taxonomy",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2607.19790/2607.19790v1/figures/taxonomy_boundaries.png",
                "caption": "Figure 2:Examples of the task boundary inTrace.Left:Changing\nextremum direction modifies only a bounded query argument and therefore\nremains within one boxplot task.Center:Adding a conjunctive\nattribute changes the candidate predicate and selected set, producing a new\nicon-filtering task.Right:Changes to board dimensions, layout, and\nvisual treatment remain generation parameters because the reachability\nprogram and reward contract are unchanged.",
                "position": 783
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "header": "4TheTraceEnvironment",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2607.19790/2607.19790v1/figures/reachable_region_pipeline.png",
                "caption": "Figure 3:End-to-end construction of aTraceinstance. Four-neighbor\nreachability is computed over the semantic cell board, and the resulting\nstate determines the typed answer, rendered image, prompt, scorer, and\nreplayable instance trace.",
                "position": 934
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2607.19790/2607.19790v1/x3.png",
                "caption": "Figure 4:Composition ofTraceacross 11 visual domains. The panels report\nthe number of task programs and scene grammars in each domain, together with\nthe overall distribution of answer interfaces.",
                "position": 955
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2607.19790/2607.19790v1/x4.png",
                "caption": "Figure 5:Distribution of task-program operations across visual domains.\nCell labels report the number of tasks assigned to each operation family,\nwhile color indicates the corresponding within-domain share. Assignments are\nexhaustive and multi-label.",
                "position": 985
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2607.19790/2607.19790v1/x5.png",
                "caption": "Figure 6:Answer-preserving realizations of a fixed semantic graph. Theme,\ntypeface, layout, non-answer context, and raster treatment vary while the\nprompt, topology, query, and typed answer remain unchanged.",
                "position": 1019
            }
        ]
